Post title: Moodle Navigation Expand and Collapse Menu
Post description: We are upgrading from Moodle 2.9 to Moodle 3.15 and have custom pages outside of Moodle, that we have built that replicates the navigation structure used in Moodle 2.9. This navigation works in 2.9. However, when moving to 3.15 this navigation menu is broken as it won't expand or collapse. This is the code that we used to get it to work in 2.9. 
```text
YUI().use('node', function(Y) {
     M.util.load_flowplayer();
     setTimeout("fix_column_widths()", 20);
     M.yui.galleryversion="2010.04.08-12-35";
     Y.use("core_dock","moodle-block_navigation-navigation",function() {

    M.block_navigation.init_add_tree({"id":"5","instance":"5","candock":false
    });

});
```
 I noticed that YUI is going away for 3.15. So how do I call the tree navigation so it would work? I have searched help and tried the suggestions in the documentation, but didn't work. I have tried putting this into my php, but didn't work. $PAGE->requires->js_call_amd('core/tree', 'Tree', 'ins5'); Any help would be appreciated.
